The paper discusses a security architecture for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of cryptography and key handshaking schemes, which could be categorized under information theory (cs.IT). The proposed architecture also considers the limitations of resources of the tiny sensors, which could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS).
